article.headline: Harvard 58, San Jose State 53
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Matt Stehle scored 14 points, and three other Harvard players scored in double figures Tuesday to lead the previously winless Crimson to a 58-53 victory over San Jose State. Harvard (1-11) made 11 of its last 13 foul shots, while San Jose State (5-5) missed its last five. The Crimson led 30-24 at halftime, but the Spartans rallied to lead on several occasions in the second half. Harvard took the lead for good on a three-point play by Stehle with 1:56 remaining. Two free throws by Graham Beatty at 1:30 and two by Michael Beal at 0:59 gave the Crimson a 52-47 advantage. The Spartans trailed by just two points at 55-53 with 4.5 seconds remaining, but Kevin Rogus made three of four foul shots to ensure the victory. Beal, Rogus and Jason Norman each scored 11 points for Harvard. Stehle and Norman tied for the game high in rebounds with five each. San Jose State's Phil Calvert scored a game-high 15 points and was the only Spartan to score in double figures. The Crimson committed 25 turnovers, while San Jose turned the ball over 19 times.
